Mixed reactions as popular Nigerian bestselling author, Reno Omokri, recently took to his verified Instagram account to release a video of a suspected unknown gunman who was nabbed by the Nigerian security operative in the southeastern region.
He used the world’s most popular photo-sharing platform, Instagram, to inform his followers about what is going on in the southeast, he captioned the photo with these words below;
“To those who claim that Fulanis and Hausa are masquerading as unknown gunmen in the southeast to give southerners a bad name, please watch this video of a suspected unknown gunman nabbed in the southeast.
Listen to him carefully, does he look or sound Fulani or Hausa?
Check out the screenshot of the post below

As expected, shortly after the video went viral, social media users slid to the comment section to react to the post from a different perspective.
